column1: # ID - sample id in SRA database
# disease - control, PD (Parkinson's disease), PDD (Parkinson's disease with dementia), DLB (dementia with Lewy bodies), MSA (multiple system atrophy)
# tissue - BA9 prefrontal cortex, putamen, anterior cingulate cortex, SNc(substantia nigra pars compacta), VTA (ventral tegmental area)
# age - the age of the patient (from 45 to 102, with NA values)
# GC_content_quality - good, middle, bad (the quality according to FastQC reports)
# SNCA_clin_mutations - mutations with unsertain significance in SNCA gene in format 1G>C (position previous nucleotide > current nucleotide)
# LRRK2_clin_mutations - mutations with unsertain significance in LRRK2 gene in format 1G>C (position previous nucleotide > current nucleotide)
# GBA_clin_mutations - mutations with unsertain significance in GBA gene in format 1G>C (position previous nucleotide > current nucleotide)
# PRKN_clin_mutations - mutations with unsertain significance in PRKN gene in format 1G>C (position previous nucleotide > current nucleotide)
# sample_id - sample id according to authors of the dataset (case/patient with number)
